title: 1992 Porsche 911 Carrera RS

This 1992 Porsche 911 Carrera RS spent time in Japan before it was brought to the US and Federalized in 2013, and it is finished in Rubystone over Black and Rubystone multi-tone leather. It is powered by a 3.6-liter flat-six paired with a five-speed manual transaxle, and other equipment includes a Fister muffler, a seam-welded chassis, a limited-slip differential, an aluminum front trunk lid, a speed-activated rear spoiler, magnesium 17″ Cup wheels, adjustable Bilstein coilovers, and fixed-back Recaro bucket seats with Rubystone seatbelts. The tires and oil lines were recently replaced. This 964 911 Carrera RS is now offered on dealer consignment with a clean Carfax report and a clean Pennsylvania title.

The Carrera RS was reintroduced with the 964 chassis and featured a seam-welded bodyshell as well as an aluminum front trunk lid, rolled fenders, and thinner side and rear windows than those used on the standard Carrera.

This example is finished in Rubystone (L82N), and the hood, right door, and rear quarter panels have been repainted. The car features faux fog lights, side marker lamps, dual side mirrors, and a speed-activated rear spoiler. Clear paint-protection film has been applied to the bodywork aside from the roof and engine lid.

Magnesium 17″ Cup wheels were recently mounted with Michelin Pilot Sport tires. The Carrera RS’s ride height is lower than that of a standard 964, and it also featured stiffer springs and adjustable anti-sway bars. Stopping power is provided by an anti-lock system featuring four-piston calipers over cross-drilled rotors at all four corners.

The fixed-back Recaro bucket seats have Rubystone seatbelts and are trimmed in Black and Rubystone multi-tone leather. Interior amenities include roll-up windows, door pull straps, and a heater. The car was delivered from the factory without airbags, air conditioning, carpeting, or sound-deadening material.

The leather-wrapped four-spoke steering wheel frames a central tachometer, a replacement 300-km/h speedometer, a clock, and gauges for fuel level, oil level, oil temperature, and oil pressure. The six-digit odometer shows 76k kilometers (~47k miles), fewer than 500 of which were added under current ownership.

The 3.6-liter M64/03 flat-six was equipped from the factory with a lightened flywheel and was rated at 260 horsepower and 229 lb-ft of torque. Additional features include a sport-tuned Bosch engine management system and a cooling fan driven by a single belt. The to- and from-tank oil hoses were replaced in February 2024.

Power is sent to the rear wheels through a G50 five-speed manual transaxle that features steel synchronizers, closer ratios than the standard Carrera, and an asymmetrical limited-slip differential. A Fister Sport Exhaust muffler has been added.

The Carfax report shows no accidents or damage.

Filed under: 964
